info: Halfway through their set, as the band were playing 'Fluorescent Adolescent', the sound from the main stage speakers cut out. After a short period of confusion an announcer addressed the crowd to say there would be a short break as technical problems were sorted. After ten minutes, the band finally returned to play 'If You Were There, Beware' (during which the sound cut out as well) and finish their set. Crying Lightning played at soundcheck.
